@startuml
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

participant "User" as user
participant "MutatingWebhook\n[Cluster Control Layer]" as webhook #CCEEFF
participant "Scheduler-Extender\n[Cluster Control Layer]" as sched #CCEEFF
participant "Device Plugin\n[Node Agent Layer]" as dp #CCFFCC
participant "HAMi-Core\n[Container Isolation Layer]" as core #FFFFCC
database "Physical GPU" as gpu

== Node Startup: Device Spec Reporting ==

dp -> sched : Write Node Annotation\nhami.io/node-nvidia-register\n(UUID / VRAM / Compute / Model)

== User Submits Pod ==

user -> webhook : Submit Pod\n(nvidia.com/gpu + gpumem)
webhook -> webhook : Rewrite schedulerName\n(force hami-scheduler)
webhook -> sched : Hand off to hami-scheduler

== Scheduling Decision ==

sched -> sched : Read Node Annotation\nSelect target node and GPU UUID
sched -> dp : Write Pod Annotation\nhami.io/vgpu-devices-allocated\n(UUID + VRAM quota + compute quota)

== Device Allocation and Container Start ==

dp -> dp : Read Pod Annotation\nGet GPU UUID and quotas
dp -> gpu : Mount /dev/nvidia*
note over dp : Allocate response injects:\n• hostPath mount libvgpu.so\n• hostPath mount ld.so.preload → /etc/ld.so.preload\n• CUDA_DEVICE_MEMORY_LIMIT_<index>\n• CUDA_DEVICE_SM_LIMIT
core -> gpu : CUDA API call\n(OOM if quota exceeded)

@enduml
